<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,978,1284]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1218,1244]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The characteristic dorsal pattern with black elytra and orange, transverse macula, allows the differentiation of this species from other members of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
